cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with differentially private algorithms for empirical risk minimization, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and lower bounds, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
